Lygephila mirabilis
).

Male genitalia ( Figs 11, 12 ). Symmetrical. Uncus long, narrow, evenly curved, with fine tip, valva narrow, elongated; ampulla long, narrow, rod-like, located subapically; aedeagus straight, long, narrow, cylindrical; vesica membranous, multidiverticulate, medial part has numerous diverticula variable in shape and size, terminal tube long, membranous (
Fig. 12
).

Female genitalia (
Figs 17–20
). Ovipositor large, papillae anales hairy with long setae on apical edges. Apophyses anteriores relatively short, apophyses posteriores thin, longer than apophyses anteriores. Antrum long, dilated posteriorly, ostium broad, posterior margin with small U-shaped cleft. Corpus bursae membranous, ovoid.
